Sorry I've been so long replying, I've really been swamped lately.  I
have no objections to using the parts of ACM that can be fit into
our kernel/driver model.  ACM has come a long way since the last time
I looked at it (~1992).  I haven't had time to look at it, so I don't
know what the code looks like as far as modularity goes.  The 3 things
it has that we will probably want to look at taking are....

1) Flight model
2) 3D graphics code and scenery
3) HSI

If we can lift these without having to take on the entire program structure
I'd be happy.  For each of the above we'd need to convert to a flight
gear driver, and replace X calls with fggrx calls, we'll also need to
determine what variables need to be globally accesable to all drivers.

Changes I've made to my code recently include...

1)  Attempted MMX-like support
2)  Started X and DJGPP (allegro) display routines

