3)  Finish X and DJGPP display routines (add palette management)
4)  Add OS\2 display routines
5)  Cobble together a quick attitude indicator and compass
7)  Take the slew model for a test flight.

Once I've finished the display routines, a volunteer can add Windows and
Mac support.  Once the test flight is done, flight model, 3D and instrument
development can begin.  Once again, I'm swamped, so I don't when I'll get around
to this stuff.

