The neat part about it is that it comes with a 56Mb (that's
*megabytes*) compressed data base of coastal, river, lake outlines for
the entire globe.  They merged data from two public databases to get
their data set.  Have a look at their web page for more info ...

Elevation data is not included as far as I can tell.

This again would be down the road a ways, but we might want to look at
setting up an internet scenery server.  For the lucky net-connected
pilots, flightgear could automatically fetch surrounding scenery and
cache it locally.  This way you wouldn't have to store gajillions of
megabytes of scenery locally ...

I will stop before I get too far ahead of myself ... :-)

